    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.1115A/1376: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-09">February 9,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received February 9—10:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>900. American interests, Far East, internees. Legation’s 743,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d820fn3">Dated February 1, <ref target="#pg_959">p.
                        959</ref>.</note> first paragraph. Swiss Consulate General telegraphs:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Japanese authorities proceeded January 31 internment 100 Americans
                            without families or having Asiatic wife. Latter case husband only
                            interned. Installation camp far from complete but Japanese authorities
                            promised early completion arrangements. About 500 employees Shanghai
                            Municipal Council mostly British informed February 1st would be gathered
                            February 9th various school buildings.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
